taverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5447.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN Adv. Points and classes...</span><hr size=1> As you accumulate points in a theme, you unlock a tier of items you can buy.  Top is 1492 (I think).  You can spend all points from all camps at any camp, but in order to get inital access to those items, you have to adventure in that particular theme enough.  Tak's best armor is plate, Guk is Leather etc.  All themes have different types of times though at different levels.  So, you can get plate armor at guk, but the best plate armor is at tak.  <br>
My suggestion, pick a theme that offeres the single best upgrade then get it to 1492 and then do whatever.  Example, I focused on Tak, now I have 1492.  I bought my nice BP, and can get nice rings, earrings etc from that theme.  However, to get the full benefit of the expansion you really need 1150 in all themes.  Each theme has one particualr augment at the 1150 or 1492 that is especially nice.  Like a 20hp/20mana augment that will go in any slot at guk, or a 40hp from Ruj etc.  If you get 1492 in your armor type, then augment from the other areas you will reap the best benefit for time spent.  IMO the bps are the nicest upgrades.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=624937" target="top">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=624937</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
